Peru Stocks: Candente, Credicorp, Maple Energy, Panoro, Volcan

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-07-12T18:49:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-12/peru-stocks-candente-credicorp-maple-energy-panoro-volcan.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 2:13 p.m.  New York  time.  The  Lima  General Index rose 0.8 percent to 19,922.30. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index gained 1 percent to 2,531.21.  Industrial and banking stocks rebounded as U.S. shares
gained in New York, Jose Luis Bustamante, head of trading at
Cartisa SAB, said in a telephone interview.  Maple Energy Plc. (MPLE)  , the oil and natural gas
producer with operations in Peru, rose 4 percent to $1.03 after
crude advanced in New York.  Grana y Montero SA (GRAMONC1)  (GRAMONC1 PE),
Peru’s largest construction firm, gained 2 percent to 5.51 soles
after Peru’s President  Alan Garcia  said the company will start
building the $600 million second stage of Lima’s overhead
railway next week.  Credicorp Ltd. (BAP)  , Peru’s largest
financial services company, climbed 1.3 percent to $86.  Copper and zinc miners gained as the metals advanced in New
York and  London .  Candente Copper Corp. (DNT)  , a Canadian exploration
company, jumped 10 percent to $1.49.  Panoro Minerals Ltd. (PML)  , a Canadian copper and gold exploration company, rose 2.1
percent to 48 cents. Sociedad Minera Cerro Verde SA (CVERDEC1
PE), a unit of Freeport-McMoRan Copper & Gold Inc., gained 1.2
percent to $37.25. Volcan Cia Minera SAA (VOLCABC1 PE), Peru’s
largest zinc producer, climbed 1.1 percent to 2.88 soles.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alex Emery  in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  